    "b-routing-overlay-p1-15": {
      "id": "b-routing-overlay-p1-15",
      "flavour": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "packages/canvas/src/connectors/connection-cascade.ts",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/connectors/connection-cascade.ts"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " is a separate, purely-computational module for the live interaction surface around making and re-pointing connections — it is not the routing algorithm itself, but the logic that decides where a connector endpoint should snap while a person is dragging it. Since the P3 geometry move (OBJECT-DEF-OVERHAUL.md (retired; see git history), D4) it carries exactly ONE port from BlockSuite's "
        },
        {
          "insert": "connector-manager.ts",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ": "
        },
        {
          "insert": "resolveConnectionCascade",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/connectors/connection-cascade.ts",
              "symbol": "resolveConnectionCascade"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (from upstream "
        },
        {
          "insert": "renderConnector",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "'s decision cascade). The outline polygons and 4-cardinal anchor projection the cascade consumes moved into "
        },
        {
          "insert": "objects/geometry.ts",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/objects/geometry.ts"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " — the defs own their outline geometry now — and the connectors slice reaches them through the single allowed boundary edge: the import-boundaries test pins the connectors slice's "
        },
        {
          "insert": "objects/",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " imports to exactly "
        },
        {
          "insert": "connectors/connection-cascade.ts -> ../objects/geometry",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (a pure, React-free module; connectors must never import def components). The port remains algorithm-only: no canvas-paint, no GfxController/grid search, no rotation support. Its current behavior also deliberately excludes section interiors from the inside snap tier while keeping section anchors and outlines valid."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-routing-overlay-p2-16": {
      "id": "b-routing-overlay-p2-16",
      "flavour": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
